subsection.p:
For consistency in notation to describe the tendency of a function (as opposed to the value of a function),
we use limits to describe unbounded behavior.

   \lim_{x \to -\infty} f(x) &= -\infty & \text{means $f(x) \to -\infty$ as $x \to -\infty$}
   \lim_{x \to -\infty} f(x) &= \infty & \text{means $f(x) \to +\infty$ as $x \to -\infty$}
   \lim_{x \to \infty} f(x) &= -\infty & \text{means $f(x) \to -\infty$ as $x \to +\infty$}
   \lim_{x \to \infty} f(x) &= \infty & \text{means $f(x) \to +\infty$ as $x \to +\infty$}

